-1 'BLIZZARD ENTERTAINMENT'~
[Note: This entry must not be removed or altered.]

Some ideas used in the Diablo II PC game have been altered to use
here. These ideas in no way are used for economical activities nor
steal the overall theme of the Diablo Series. As such, there are used
for unreal characters in an unreal world mainly for recreational
activities.

                 Blizzard Entertainment
                    P.O. Box 18979
                   Irvine, CA 92623


#e'Diablo II, the best game of its genre which we ever play.#n' - The Imms
~

-1 'PROPOSED CHANGES'~

- Angels and Demons will be taken out of normal classes and become 'SPECIAL CLASSES'. I.e/
  a person can RECLASS into one if he meets certain requirements.
- Everyone will now start off at neutral alignment. However, depending on who you kill and/or
  deeds that you do can raise/lower your alignment.
- Kingdoms will be replaced with a politics systems that is based on the roman empire, the
  british royalty system and the anarchy.
- You now take damage for Non K/P Guard Cancels, around the same for Guard Instances...
  however all grooves now get a much more powerful bonus during this same round.
~

-1 BLOCK AUTOGUARD~
.
   For the first time in the utopia series, players can now manually (or automatically) block
incoming attacks by using the #wblock#n command. Doing so will put the character in a defensive
state where all attacks will only do half damage (*) to them. Note though that all countering
and evasive measures will be reduced to 0% and you will be unable to do anything for a round.
   There are two exceptions to this system. One is AutoBlocking. Depending on your vitality
level in correspondance to your opponent's dexterity level, there is a chance that you will
automatically block their attack with #wGUARD INSTANCE#n. This only works for that one
particular attack and the player doesn't suffer any lag penalties. The other one is when you
use the block command just before the opponent attacks you. Here, you will #wGUARD CANCEL#n
the attack and can immediately counter attack with a bonus to your strength and mind
stats.
   Otherwise, everytime you manually block an attack (not melee except in rare cases), your
block meter will be reduced by a specified % that is determined by the strength of the attack,
your vitality, etc. If your block meter reaches 0, then you will be #wGUARD BREAK#n. Here,
your manual/automatic blocking is broken by the opponent causing you to be dazed for a round.
Also as the meter tries to recover, all attacks will do 25% more damage unto you so as a hint
you should always pay attention to your block meter.
   AutoGuard is a feature some attacks have. With this, you will automatically block the
opponent's attack receiving no damage, and counter with the designated skill. Zanretsu Ken
and aragami have an autoguard feature for instance.

#P(*) Melee damage will do quarter damage instead of half.#n
~

-1 GROOVES~
.
   Just like from the popular SNK Vs Capcom series, Grooves represents fighting styles that
are associated with the power meter bar. Each groove is unique in its features and can make
or break a fighter's chance of survival.

#wDodge          - #gDodge your opponent's or their striker's next attack.  #w(Level 1)
#wSuperCancel    - #gUse dazzling energy to instantly recover from your next technique. #w(Level 1)
#wCounterPush    - #gA complex form of blocking that uses one's body to stop a fight. #w(Level 1)
#wEmergencyRoll  - #gImmediately roll back onto your feet from a stunned or woozy state. #w(Level 1)
                 #gCan use #wEroll #gfor short.
#wEmergencyFlip  - #gLand back on your feet from a catapulting move (1 stock) or recover
                 from a mortal state (2 stocks). #w(Level 1 - 2)
                 #gCan use #wEflip #gfor short.
#wRetort         - #gCounter your opponent's or their striker's next attack. #w(Level 2)

#P(*) - In K, A, P, and S groove, #wDodge, CounterPush, SuperCancel and EmergencyRoll #Pwill
cost you 1/3 of your bar and #wRetort #Pwill cost you 2/3 of your bar. Note that this can't
be done with TimeStop.#n

#CSyntax - #PChoose '<GROOVE LETTER> GROOVE' 
         #CE.g #yChoose #w'C GROOVE'#n

#wSEE ALSO: HELP #y'C GROOVE', 'S GROOVE', 'A GROOVE', 'K GROOVE', 'N GROOVE', 
               'M GROOVE', 'P GROOVE', 'GROOVE EXAMPLES'#n
~

-1 'GROOVE EXAMPLES'~
.
#pC GROOVE -  #w+Lvl #C1 #y>>>#e>>>>>>#w+
            #w+Lvl #C2 #y>>>>>>>>>#w+
            #w+Lvl #C3   #o<#wMAX#o>  #w+

#pN GROOVE -  #w[*   #y||||#e|||||#w]
            #w[**  #y||||||#e|||#w]
            #w[#yPOW #C-----#e----#w]

#pS GROOVE -  #w[#y++++++#e++++#w]
            #w[#R+++#yPMAX#R++#e+#w]

#pK GROOVE -  #w<<#y^^^^#e^^^^^^#w>>
            #w<<#R^^^#y#uRAGE#n#R^#e^^#w>>
            * - ^ are really tildles

#pA GROOVE -  #w[+#y>>>#e>>>>>>>#w+]
            #w[T#C<<<<<<<#e<<<#wS]#n

#pP GROOVE -  #w<-#C)))#e)))))))#w->
            #w||-#sS=U#e=P=E=R#w->

#pM GROOVE -  #w[#o|#C0#o____***-#e--#w)
            #w[#o|#C2#o____*#e**---#w)#g>>
            #w||----#e-#y> #CPOWER #y<#e-#w-----||#n

N.B/ If the person doesn't have ANSI on, then #ethis colour#n won't be shown.
~

-1 'P GROOVE'~
.
   #w#uADVANCED PARRYING GAUGE SYSTEM#n

Your character's gauge will build up as you attack. You can perform a dodge using
33% of the groove bar or a retort using 66%. When it is fully charged up, the
#wsuper#n mode will be activated and you can perform a Level 1 (NOT 2 or 3)
Desperation attack. Also in this mode, your counter rate will be increased, and
your tech damage will raise slightly.

It is to be noted that at later pkills, this doesn't fill up as fast as other
groves, but by performing guard cancels... one can execute a #yguard counter#n
that returns some of the damage back to the foe. The #yguard counter's#n strength
increases with pkills.

The following actions are available with P-Groove:

#c- #wStagger: #yUse people's dash like attacks against them. #P(Auto)

#c- #wPriority Exemption: #yIf both you and the opponent are doing attacks that has
  the same priority level, then you can use your battle knowledge to get an exemption
  over his thus establishing a counter attack.

#c- #wGuard Tactics: #yUse people's desperation attacks to fill up your bar somewhat,
  providing that you block the attack. #P(Auto)#n
~

-1 'M GROOVE'~
.
   #w#uMASTER GROOVE GAUGE SYSTEM#n

Your character's gauge will build up as you attack. You can charge the gauge up to level 3.
Depending on the gauge level you can perform 3 levels of Desperation attacks.

Also you can perform Power MODE by pressing activate (*). When your character is in the Power MAX
condition, your attack becomes more powerful.

The following actions are available with M-Groove:

#c- #wStagger: #yUse people's dash like attacks against them. #P(Auto)

#c- #wPriority Exemption: #yIf both you and the opponent are doing attacks that has
  the same priority level, then you can use your battle knowledge to get an exemption
  over his thus establishing a counter attack.

#c- #wQuick Recovery: #yUse your knowledge of Safe Falling to quickly get back onto your feet following
  a stunning attack. #P(Auto)

#c- #wSafe Fall: #yWith this technique, you will always land back on your feet from being catapulted
  into the air, thus taking no damage. #P(Auto)

#c- #wDash: #ySimilar to Paladins' charge, but this can be done at anytime.

#c- #wRun: #yUse this technique to run into anyone within the vicinity. Note that it is wearing.

#c- #wTactical Recovery: #yWhen you are stunned and are not in a critical state, you can use this
  to become immuned to all attacks while taking the time to get back up. #P(Auto)

#c- #wAerial Strike: #yThis aerial technique makes it harder for your opponents to dodge, counter
  or block your jumping attacks. #P(Auto)

#P(*) You can't use this command until you have selected a T.O.P. mode.#n
~

-1 'C GROOVE'~
.
   #w#uSUPER COMBO LEVEL GAUGE SYSTEM#n

Your character's gauge will build up as you attack. You can charge the gauge up to level 3.
Depending on the gauge level you can perform 3 levels of Desperation attacks.

The following actions are available with C-Groove:

#c- #wDash: #ySimilar to Paladins' charge, but this can be done at anytime.

#c- #wTactical Recovery: #yWhen you are stunned and are not in a critical state, you can use this
  to become immuned to all attacks while taking the time to get back up. #P(Auto)

#c- #wAerial Strike: #yThis aerial technique makes it harder for your opponents to dodge, counter
  or block your jumping attacks. #P(Auto)

#c- #wPriority Exemption: #yIf both you and the opponent are doing attacks that has the same priority
  level, then you can use your battle knowledge to get an exemption over his thus establishing a
  counter attack. Note however that P groove's version beats this one. #P(Auto)

#c- #wPriority Charge: #yYour groove bar fills out the fastest out of all the groove systems. #P(Auto)#n
~

-1 'S GROOVE'~
.
   #w#uGROOVE GAUGE SYSTEM#n

You can charge the gauge by using the #wCharging#n command. In this state, you are completely
defenseless and is unable to do anything else. You can come out of this state by using #wCharging#n
again. It also builds up as you attack. When the Groove Gauge is full, your character's attack
becomes a bit more powerful for awhile and you can use a Level 1 Desperation move.

When your character's life is low, you can use unlimited Level 1 Desperation Moves. Take note though
that in this state, they will lag you alot more than normal. Also, if your groove bar is full in this
state, you can do a Level 1 - 3 Desperation attack with no lag penalty.

The following actions are available with S-Groove:

#c- #wRun: #yUse this technique to run into anyone within the vicinity. Note that it is wearing.

#c- #wSmall Jump: #yThis techniques protects you from the trip command and has a good chance of dodging
  low attacks. #P(Auto)#n
~

-1 'A GROOVE'~
.
   #w#uGROOVE GAUGE SYSTEM#n

The gauge will build up as you attack. You can perform a Level 1 Desperation Move by using half of this
gauge. When the gauge is full, you can perform a #wCustom Combo#n by using the #wTimeStop#n command. In,
this state, all of your techniques will be lagless and your evasion/counter rate will DRAMATICALLY
INCREASE. The penalty from this however is your strength will DRAMATICALLY DECREASE.

   #w#uCUSTOM COMBO#n

This represents ANY move that your character can do, including Lvl 1 - 3 Desperation Attacks, that can
be done over and over... and over again. The only penalties you have with this are if the move has a
timer. Apart from that, use strategy to rip apart the opponent.

The following actions are available with A-Groove:

#c- #wDash: #ySimilar to Paladins' charge, but this can be done at anytime.

#c- #wSafe Fall: #yWith this technique, you will always land back on your feet from being catapulted
  into the air, thus taking no damage. #P(Auto)

#c- #wQuick Recovery: #yUse your knowledge of Safe Falling to quickly get back onto your feet following
  a stunning attack. #P(Auto)#n
~

-1 'K GROOVE'~
.
   #w#uRAGE GAUGE SYSTEM#n

The gauge will build up as you get attacked or perform #wJust Defense#n (see below). When the gauge
is full, your character will be in Rage MAX condition for awhile. During Rage MAX, your character's
attacks become MUCH more powerful and you can perform a Level 1 Desperation Attack before 10 pkills,
a Lvl 1 or 2 Attack at 10 - 19 pkills, or a Lvl 1 - 3 attack from 20 pkills onwards.

   #w#uJUST DEFENSE#n

Just Defense is a technique for blocking an opponent's attack. To perform it, wait to #wblock#n until
just before the attack touches your fighter. If you perform Just Defense successfully, your
character will not be hit back, or take Guard or Guard Break damage. Also, your character can recover
some health back.

The following actions are available with K-Groove:

#c- #wRun: #yUse this technique to run into anyone within the vicinity. Note that it is wearing.

#c- #wTactical Recovery: #yWhen you are stunned and are not in a critical state, you can use this
  to become immuned to all attacks while taking the time to get back up. #P(Auto)

#c- #wSmall Jump: #yThis techniques protects you from the trip command and has a good chance of dodging
  low attacks. #P(Auto)#n
~

-1 'N GROOVE'~
.
   #w#uADVANCED POWER GAUGE SYSTEM#n

The gauge will build up as you attack. When the gauge is full, you gain one level of Desperation
attacks. You can accumulate up to three levels of Desperation Attacks.

Also you can perform Power MAX by pressing activate (*). When your character is in the Power MAX
condition, your attack becomes more powerful. If you have any addition gauge levels when your
character is in the Power MAX condition, you can perform a Level 2 or 3 Desperation Attack (providing
you have the pkills). Note that the Power max dissappears after perform a Desperation Attack or a
few rounds.

Apart from this, you can perform a Level * move if you have the number of * showing in your groove
bar. E.g/ You need a *** to do a Lvl 3 Desperation Move and a ** for a Lvl 2 one.

The following actions are available with N-Groove:

#c- #wRun: #yUse this technique to run into anyone within the vicinity. Note that it is wearing.

#c- #wSafe Fall: #yWith this technique, you will always land back on your feet from being catapulted
  into the air, thus taking no damage. #P(Auto)

#P(*) You can't use this command until you have selected a T.O.P. mode.#n
~

0 'JUDGE SYSTEM'~
.
   Established by Julius Caeser, and maintained by the Senate and the Holy Church, the Judge
System is a complex set of rules that everyone must follow. These rules are split up into
two sets - #eForbidden #cRules#n and #wRecommended #cRules#n.

#gE.g    #o|----------------------------------------|
       #o|    #eForbidden       #o|   #wRecommended     #o|
       #o------------------------------------------
       #o| #pPiercing Techs     #o| #CHoly Techs        #o|
       #o| #pBlocking           #o| #CMagic Attacks     #o|
       #o| #pDesperation Moves  #o| #CHealing           #o|
       #o|                    #o|                   #o|
       #o------------------------------------------#n

   As can be seen from the above example, there are 4 slots with 3 of them filled. During most
months, it will just be 1 slot, a few of them 2 slots, and one month 3 slots. Take note that
laws in the Forbidden slot has priority over ones in the Recommended slot. By doing a recommended
law, the Divine Knights (Enforcers of the Laws) watching the battle will reward you with #wJudge
Points#n. Otherwise, if you do a forbidden law, expect SWIFT and DEADLY retaliation from the
judges, such as penalizing your abilities, damaging you with their POWERFUL divine techniques
(that ALWAYS destroy equipment even through maintenance), or automatically letting your
opponent win the battle and throwing you in jail.

#wSEE ALSO: HELP 'JUDGE POINTS', 'JUDGE MASTER', 'ANTILAW CARDS'#n
~

0 'JUDGE POINTS'~
.
   By doing recommended laws in battle, the Divine Knight (or Judge Master) watching the battle
will award you Judge Points. As you accumulate enough of these points, you can buy things that
are otherwise difficult, or even impossible to get.
   The list of items bought with Judge Points are as follows:

   #o|--------------------------------------------|
   #o| #gItem                 #o|   #gJudge Points      #o|
   #o----------------------------------------------
   #o| #w1 Training Point     #o|   #y2 Judge Points    #o|
   #o| #w1 Gen Level          #o|   #y5 Judge Points    #o|
   #o| #w5 Summons Point      #o|  #y20 Judge Points    #o|
   #o| #wOmega Blade #P(1 Use)  #o|  #y25 Judge Points    #o|
   #o| #wArmageddon  #P(#y*#P)      #o|  #y25 Judge Points    #o|
   #o| #wAlpha Bahamut        #o|  #y50 Judge Points    #o|
   #o| #wThe End              #o|  #y99 Judge Points    #o|
   #o----------------------------------------------

#P(#y*#P) #c- Also gives you 1 Pkill#n
~

0 'JUDGE MASTER'~
.
   If you are very lucky (or unlucky depending on the situation), you may be blessed with
an audience of Judge Master Cid himself watching your fight, instead of the normal Divine
Knights. When Judge Master Cid comes into play, your battle is now governed by #ySpecial
Laws#n, and you are granted extra Judge Points for complying with the rules. Also too,
the winner is bestowed an additional privelege as ordered by the High Priest himself.
This could involve things from extra gold, to temporary invincibilty or the High Priest
Seal (*).

(*) - A legendary item that once consumed, allow you to be unpunished by using forbidden
      rules. This only lasts for awhile though.
~

0 'ANTILAW CARDS'~
.
   Not everyone is happy with the laws established by the Senate. As such, a rogue
wizard had used his powerful magic to create powerful antilaw cards that actually has
the signature of the High Priest. With this signature, Divine Knights MUST follow the
changes at their own peril. The slight exemption to this is Judge Master Cid with his
#yspecial laws#n.
   There are 2 types of antilaw cards: #wwhite#n and #eblack#n ones. Black ones remove
an existing law from the law slot if they are the same, while White ones add a new
law into the law slot (providing there is a free one). The exception to this are the
R antilaw cards (like R1, R2) that remove all laws of that level from the law slot,
and the rare Allmighty R card that removes ALL laws.
~

0 KINGDOMS~
.
   These are the usual player run kingdoms in godwars type muds. 

#wprince      - #oGive a kingdom mate the power to induct new members
#winduct      - #oThe ability to put a new member in your kingdom
#woutcast     - #oLeave your kingdom in disgust
#wkdeposit    - #oDespoit money into your kingdom treasury
#wviewkingdom - #oSee the stats of the kingdom members online
#wkingdomlist - #oSee the stats of all the kingdoms
#wcapture     - #oCatch an enemy and throw them in the dungeon
#wlands       - #oSee which areas each kingdom currently have control over
#wobtain      - #oThe ability to invade and claim an area if not beaten in awhile
#wrelease     - #oFree a fellow kingdom member who has been captured
#wmemberlist  - #oSee who is in what kingdom by using kingdom1, kingdom2, ..., or 
              kingdom4 as the arguments. E.g/ memberlist kingdom3

   #eN.B/ Kingdom members can't hurt each other.

#wSEE ALSO: #CHELP INVASION, KINGDOMWARS, KINGDOMSTUFF, SALVATION, KINGDOMDIRS
        'THE REBORN', 'LOST ONES', 'HEAVENLY CLAN'#n
~

0 'HEAVENLY CLAN'~
.
#wLeader:      #eTaco
#wPurpose:     #eTo keep the seal broken between earth and the demon realm, so
             that evil can continue to ravage the land.
#wAlignment:   #eNeutral to Evil
#wClasses Req: #eAll, as long as the align is neutral or evil; Angels are not allowed.
#wMajor Goal:  #eTo destroy the earth and recreate it in the true image.
#wMinor Goals: #eTo corrupt followers of Good.
             To improve the terrains of their stronghold so various affects can
             be utilized at anytime.
             To convert and raise fallen ones to assist in battle
             To get ore and minerals for powerful armor (+str & +min) equipment.

#wSEE ALSO: #RHELP 'HEAVENLY STORY'#n
~

0 'HEAVENLY STORY'~
.
For a thousand years, the imperial court had ruled.
But the forbbiden Seal was broken in a lust for power,
and its days of glory drew to a rapid close...
 
Clouds gathered overhead,
and the land was engulfed in a perpetual darkness...
 
The light of neither star nor moon could pierce
the night, and a giant tempest arose fron the eerie
blackness to level all that stood before it....
 
When the winds had passed, all the remained
was a Court in ruins, and a city devoid of life...

The Heavenly Clan has returned...
~

0 SALVATION~
.
#wLeader:      #yNihil
#wPurpose:     #yBy Decree of The Gods, To lance the festering boil
             of corruption with the shining blade of righteous faith.
#wAlignment:   #yNeutral or Good
#wClass limit: #yNo Demons, Fiends, Undead Knights, Necromancers, Vampires,
             or Drow.
#wMajor Goal:  #yTo crusade against the forces of evil and the ignorant and claim
             all land for the glory of the Light.
#wMinor Goals: #yTo help newbies get accustomed to the mud.
             To fight for Justice, not for power or greed.
             To raise warhorses and pegasi.
             To get ore and minerals for powerful armor (+con) equipment.

#wSEE ALSO: #CHELP 'SALVATION STORY'#n
~

0 'SALVATION STORY'~
.
   Two Hundred and thirty three years ago, in a city crumbling under its own
fetid stench, an order of watchful heroes gathered to stem the tide of darkness
covering the world.  An Evil had crept slowly into the hearts and minds of the
common people, and they began to forget what it was to be good.  The Gods,
fearing for their beloved humanity, granted these warriors extraordinary powers
so that they could seek out the source of this taint and destroy it.  Little did
the Gods know that the corruption spawned by this unknown source would first
have to be cleansed before the actual purification could begin.  They trained
hard, bringing all their powers and skills to bear in the teaching of one
another, as well as in the instruction of those who would be their successors
The Order became a beacon in the dark, burning away filth and corruption
with the light of their faith, slaving in their war against this unknown evil.
   Nine generations passed, the Order, secretly called Salvation by the
population of this world, is mustering their forces to once and for all strike 
this corruption from their land.  If they succeed in this, perhaps then they
can begin the real task of rooting out the source of this Evil...
~

0 'LOST ONES'~
.
#wLeader:      #CBryce
#wPurpose:     #CTo live for the fight under the code of the warrior.
#wAlignment:   #CNeutral
#wClass Req:   #CDisciplined based classes.
#wMajor Goal:  #CTo bring an ever lasting turmoil between good and evil so the glory
             of battle can last forever.
#wMinor Goals: #CTo become one with nature, body, and soul.
             To build modern tools of warfare.
             To train archers, swordsmen and sergeants.
             To get ore and minerals for powerful armor (+dex & +agi) equipment.

#wSEE ALSO: #yHELP 'LOST STORY'#n
~

0 'LOST STORY'~
.
   If you are reading this, then you are interested in learning more about the
warriors known as the lost ones. We live under the words of Vivaldi,
the samurai and myself.. a former knight. We do not live for glory nor wealth
for in the battlefield, there are no such things. Cowardice is deplored. 
Justice is admired. For the lost ones, discipline is life and all other things 
matter not. We live to fight. Our purpose is to maintain the balance between
good and evil, so that the fight will live on.. to breed more warriors.
~

0 'THE REBORN'~
.
#wLeader:      #RKadiel
#wPurpose:     #RTo be hired assassins
#wAlignment:   #RNeutral
#wClass Limit: #RAll Except classes that are Aligned with good eg Angels/Paladins
#wMajor Goal:  #RTo have all lands under the control of the great reborn clan.
#wMinor Goals: #RTo take out single targets for payment.
             To spy on groups of people for payment.
             To protect other people for payment.
             To build traps and forms of illusions for their stronghold.
             To get ore and minerals for powerful armor (+eva) equipment.

#wSEE ALSO: #yHELP 'REBORN STORY'#n
~

0 'REBORN STORY'~
.
  Long time ago in a place named Divinal there was a clan of
mages. These mages fought a war with ancient Draconians, as the war
seemed to be pulling on the side of the mages the Draconians realized
a new force for them to use. After this the mages were forced to hide
in fear and in shame throughout all of Divinal. The Draconians began
to rule over the city, all the mages could do is put little pockets up
for a defense because of the new force the Draconians had, Loki a
insane werewolf the draconians had taken control of, many mages died.
  As time progressed it began to look hopeless for the mages and in 1
final attack on the captial of Divinal, where Loki and the leader of
the Draconians Bahamut where at.A group of mages in this battle figured a
ritual out that would be able to defeat the Draconians but destroy all
of Divinal, they decided they were going to die anyways so they were going to
use it.Before they used it each of them prayed to there gods,Ifrit
Thor, Tyr, Odin, and Vishnu for salvation after they commit this act.
Vishnu the only one who answered this prayer told Kadiel, the
leader of the mages, that after they died they would have to be his
minions forever and may only be set free if they can Destroy all other
Gods and set him at top and only then would he give them salvation.
Kadiel agreed. After the act was commited nearly 1,000 years later...
it is time for revenge...
~

0 INVASION~
.
   To invade a kingdom is relatively simple. Simply find the invasion room
in your kingdom or at recall, then say these magic words... providing you
have no fight timer:

#wSalvation       - #ySay Salvation
#wLost Ones       - #ySay Lostones
#wThe Reborn      - #ySay Reborn#n
#wHeavenly Clan   - #ySay Heavenly#n
~

