0 KINGDOMWARS~
.
   Think your kingdom is IT?! Think you are LEGIT! Then just don't QUIT!! Come and EXHIBIT
your maaaaaad skills in this weekly war of chaos!
   The rules are simple. Have the MOST kingdom kills at the end of the week! Simple huh?
Maybe, for see you can only get them from killing opponent kingdom members!
   So Stopping chatting with your friends, leave that for AIM, clean up the rust, its time
to win some FAME! For if you do not, then you are quite LAME! Thus the punishment you
get is quite far from TAME!
~

0 ATTRIBUTES~
.
   In the world of Utopia, the various attributes of a player have their advantages and 
disadvantages about them. Each of these will be explained in more detail below:

#w(#yStr#w)#gength - This represents the sheer power of the player. By having a higher strength,
             players can execute more damage per PHYSICAL attack and MELEE hit.

#w(#yVit#w)#gality - By training their bodies and mind in rigious environments, players of a
             high vitality can take a tremedous amount of PHYSICAL damage compared to their
             less sturble counterparts. This also have an affect in doing automatic blocks
             (guard instances).

#w(#yMin#w)#gd - This represents the intelligence of the player. By having a higher mind power,
         combined with the speed to follow their thoughts, players have a higher chance of
         countering attacks. Also to an extent, they will also execute more damage per MAGICAL attack.

#w(#ySpi#w)#grit - By mastering the secrets of the soul and the netherworlds, a player with high
           spiritual energy can take a tremedous amount of MAGICAL damage compared to their more
           earthly counterparts. This also affects the strength of your deities' summons and healing
           skills.

#w(#yDex#w)#gterity - A graceful act perfected by agile fighters, dexterity represents the player's
              ability to strike their foes more times than usual and it also affects the hitrate
              of attacks. This is also one of the attributes used for countering attacks.

#w(#yEva#w)#gsion - A graceful act perfected by agile fighters, evasion represents the player's
            ability to evade ALL attacks directed at them.

#w(#yAgi#w)#gility - A graceful act perfected by speedy fighters, agility represents how long the
             player has to wait after doing EQUIPMENT (special) techniques.

#w(#yTen#w)#gsion - This represents your character's anger. The more you get beaten up, especially
             against multiple players, the more enticed and enraged you become. When this is full,
             your anger will be released giving you a 50% bonus to all attacks. In this state, you
             can also perform a #CDoubleAttack#g with a grouped ally to cause some GRAVE damage.

#w(#yLuc#w)#gk - This attribute gives a random bonus to all the other ones, just like real Luck.#n

   All players on creation and detoxxing will start off with 30 training points and 5 points already
allocated to each stat. These can be used freely on any of the attributes BUT Luck, Tension and Agility.
However, there is one clause. There can never be more than a 25 numerical difference between ANY
two normal stats; i.e if Str is 26 and Vit is 1, then Str can't be trained anymore until Vit is. 
   With the exception of Luck, Tension and Agility, each of these stats can be increased to 99.
Agility and Tension will be set for the player at player creation and Luck will change every tick.
~

0 'ATTACK TYPES'~
.
   In utopia, all attacks are of a specific type and/or element. One attack's strength
can be the attacker's own demise against a certain foe. It is up to the wielder to grasp
the truth amongst the lies and wield it like the fable sword of Justice to smite down ALL
foes.

             #P#uAttack Types#n

#wPhysical   #o- This represents attacks of the fist, and man made objects like swords.
#wMagical    #o- This represents attacks of mystical energies, like for instance a fireball.

             #P#uAttack Types Variants#n

#wSlash      #o- This represents curving attacks from swords, axes, etc.
#wPierce     #o- This represents thrusting attacks from daggers, knives, spears, etc.
#wBlast      #o- This represents short bursts of attacks from firebreaths, fireballs etc.
#wBeam       #o- This represents charging energy attacks like lasers, beams etc.
#wSpirit     #o- This represents attacks from the netherworld, like psychic attacks.
#wNormal     #o- This represents normal attacks like those of fists and feet.
#wBlunt      #o- This represents stunning attacks from hammers, shockwaves etc.

             #P#uElemental Types#n

#PNatural    #o- For those who are still searching for their path. (NonElemental)
#RFire       #o- Fear the destructive powers of these flame embodied attacks.
#CIce        #o- May the chilly wrath of these attacks not send you to your doom.
#yThunder    #o- Strive not to be struck with terror from these swiftful attacks.
#gEarth      #o- Beware of the silent attacks of natures, for these will immbolize you.
#wHoly       #o- Have faith in the Light, else its attacks will destroy you.
#eDark       #o- NEVER underestimate evil, for its attacks are the most... feared.
#oLunar      #o- Some say this is energy from Gaia, others say it is from Luna... but it is deadly#n

#wSEE ALSO:  #oHELP 'ATTACK TYPES CONTD'#n
~

0 'ATTACK TYPES CONTD'~
.
             #P#uFocus Points#n

#wDirect     #o- A straight attack, like a jab... usually to the upper region of the body.
#wLow        #o- Usually a sweeping attack to the lower region of the body.
#wAerial     #o- Usually an attack perform in the air, like a jumpkick. 
#wOverhead   #o- Similar to a jumping attack in perspective, but is performed on the ground.
#wUppercut   #o- A powerful attack that goes from the lower to upper region of the body, like
             a Shoryuken for instance.

             #P#uAttack Priority#n

#wDirect #C<-- #wLow #C<-- #wAerial #C<-- #wUppercut #C<-- #wOverhead #C<-- #wDirect#n

#oAs can be seen from the diagram, Attacks to the immediate right counters the attack before
it. So for instance, a low attack counters a direct attack. Basically if your opponent does
an attack after you that can be countered by your own (i.e if he does a direct attack after
your low one), there is a higher chance of you evading, blocking or countering their move.#n
~

-1 OLDCHANGES~
.
- there are now new skillbuys and illusion blur/weapon guard were improved
- redemption and defiance are now self only auras
- putting on/off auras now lag you.
- all classes will have to buy hunt and stealth if they want to use them now. Also, portalling
  to someone who isn't in the same area as you with a ft will cost 25% of your mana
- status was removed and you can now choose TOP from the start
- stances are in, including the wolf stance.
- wizards can now specialize from the start and timemages got new skills
- blocking is now in so reread help block. Guard Cancel is your friend so try to master it.
- Equipment will play a MAJOR role in the customization of your character and a semi major role
  in pkilling. It also deals with generation and levels so READ HELP EQUIPMENT or HELP GENERATION
- you can now buy training points for 250k gold each, summon points now cost 50k gold and there
  are training points (TP) tokens
- you can now get any aura now and you now get one at every 10 pkills instead of 15
- although the new skillbuys can be bought, they AREN'T in it. Buy them at your own peril.
- saiyans no longer need to charge for their techs since the S groove uses it
- Expect a judge system similar to the one in final fantasy tactics advance to be in the future
- All dodging techs are now based on your evasion over your attacker's dex among other things
- All countering is now based on your dex and mind over your attacker's dex and str/mind depending
  on whether or not it is a physical or magical attack.
- luck now works and counter attacks (like the one in the team battles) are now in
- all groove stuff are in
~

-1 EQUIPMENT GENERATION~
.
   For the first time in the utopia series (well... maybe not the first time), equipment will
play a major role in your quest to become the strongest warrior. Apart from boosting (or penalizing)
your stats, they now either give affects, skills, or boths.
   All the affects have no #wLevel restriction#n. This means that you will experience the affect
as soon as you don the gear. Skills on the other hand do have #wLevel restrictions#n, and this is
where the fun begins. An example of an equipment that has a skill is shown below:

   E.g --->  #yThunder #CBlade - #wThunder Attack Bonus #y+9
                             #RStrength  #y+5
                             #CDexterity #y+7
                             #oEvasion   #y-3
                             #wLevel 2 Skill: #yLightningBlade#n

   As can be seen from the equipment, LightningBlade is a Level 2 skill. How then do we get to this
level? This is where generation comes in. Every character starts off at #wLevel 1, #CGeneration 5#n.
As you tie people in your generation range, your own will gradually become 1. Now if you tie another
Generation 1 person, you will automatically #P"level up"#n and become Generation 5 again. I.e/ If Miang
ties Ramsus and both are Gen 1 (Lvl 1), then Miang will become Lvl 2 Gen 5 and Ramsus will become
Lvl 1 Gen 2. This goes for a max of 5 Levels. However, the restriction is you can only gain and lose
generation from those with the same level as you. I.e/ A lvl 2 person won't get generation from a lvl
1 person or a lvl 3 person, etc. Bear in mind just as you can level up, you can also be brought down
a level if you are tied with a generation of 5. I.e/ If Ramsus with Lvl 2 Gen 5 is tied by Miang who
is also Lvl 2 Gen 5, Ramsus will drop down to Lvl 1 Gen 1.

   It is #y#uimperative#n that you understand this. If you don't, then read it a few more times and if you
still don't understand by then, try to ask the other players (or an admin as a last resort) for help.
~

1 NEWBIE~

As a newbie you should start by reading the help files, type "help motd"
to get a list of some of the important ones. To get a class, either
use autoclass 'class name' if it is in, or ask a player in that class to 
teach you it. Otherwise, you will have to hope an kind imm put you in the
class.

Some hints that may help you :

#w* #oClaim your newbieeq so you don't have to search for your corpse
  if you get killed.
#w* #oIf you have any problems, try asking any players from your own
  class to help you out. If theres no one on who can help you, try
  asking an imm for help.
#w* #oDon't forget to cast resistance and cast spellproof on ALL of your
  equipment.
#w* #oTurn Truesight on so you can see everything

#C#uA few things you should check out are the folowing:#n

#wHelp: #oRULES#w, #oCLASS#w, #oDETOX#w, #oSTATCAPS#w, #oPKNOW#w, #oMONEY#w, #oSTATUS#w, #oSHORTFIGHT
#wHelp: #oATTRIBUTES#w, #oMSP#w, #oMCP, #oBRIEF#w, #oKINGDOM#w, #oSPECIALBUY
#wHelp: #oTRAINING#w, #oRESCUE#w, #oWARP#w, #oARENAWATCH#w, #oSETLOGIN#w, #o'SCAVENGER HUNT'
#wHelp: #oDEITIES#w, #oALIGN#w, #oSKILLBUY#w, #oAREAPOINTS#w, #oBLOCK#w, #oGROOVES#w, #oBUY
#wHelp: #oAUCTION#w, #o'ATTACK TYPES'#w, #oMAKE#w, #oTOP#w, #oSTANCES#w
#wHelp: #oTRANSMIGRATION#w, #o'DUNGEON OF DEATH'#w, #oFORGE#w, #oRUNESHIFT#n

#wThen Type: Train

The homepage has a special section dedicated to newbies. It can be
found under HELP HOMEPAGE
~

0 BUY SELL LIST VALUE~
.
   These generic commands need no introduction (we hope). But for those who
seemily forgot or is too rich to be bothered with these 'chores', this
represents the player buying and selling 'goods' to shop keepers throughout
the lands. to a lesser extent, this can also refers to other players.
Listing is a command that can be used at the shop keepers to see what they
have for sale. Value is a command to see how much the shop keeper would pay
for your goods.
~

0 TOP~
.
     #o#uTactical Offensive Position#n

   T.O.P. is a state much like Infinity mode from Team battle that is automatically activated
at 33%, 66% or 100% respectively depending on the user's choice. In T.O.P mode, your life
gradually recovers and the player (class) now has access to moves and features that are
otherwise locked.

#yActivate - #wUse this command to set where you want your T.O.P. mode to be activated.

#wSEE ALSO: HELP 'TOP BONUS'#n
~

0 'TOP BONUS'~
.
   #RCritical Mode#n

#yEvasive Mode      - #RBeing so close to death, your dodging capabilities are improved.
#yBody Exertion     - #wBy utlizing your remaining energy, you can recover from some techniques quicker.
#yTrue Anger        - #RMake all of your techniques/skills do more damage to fuel your wrath.

   #CFocused Mode#n

#yDamage Nullifier  - #CBy analysing foes' techniques, you have a better chance to guard cancel.
#yConcentration     - #CFocus on your foe's weak points to improve your hitrate/lower misses.
#yDelayed Blow      - #CExpand some of your energy to make some techniques stronger than normal.

   #wHealthy Mode#n

#yCounter Blow      - #wThe ability to quickly retort after being damaged by an attack.
#yBody Mastery      - #wWith this comes the ability to hit harder and faster than normally possible.
#yBody Exertion     - #wBy utlizing your energy, you can recover from some techniques quicker.#n
~

