0 'ALIGN ALIGNMENT'~
	
* Everyone starts off at neutral (0) Alignment.
* Alignment goes up as you heal players, protect them from harm or decapitate evil people.
  Note that it REALLY goes up if you use life saving skills.
* Alignment goes down as you decapitate good people, steal items from people, vulture fights
  or steal spells from people (with shadowswap). Note that it REALLY goes up if you
  steal caps from people.
* As you become more good, your resilience to holy attacks improve and your weakness to
  dark attacks worsen and vice versa.

#e* NB - Everytime you reclass, you have to get an extra 10 pkills to reclass again#n
~


0 DEITIES~
.
   From the beginning of times, powerful spirits watched over the realm of Utopia.
Throughout its peak of achievements and depths of destruction, these beings had
lent their strengths to man and demon alike...
   After awhile, they were conceived as 'gods' and thus became worshipped for
the glory of obtaining power.

#o1) #CQuezacotl       #y<--- #wCounters #y--->      #o2) #CTitan
#o3) #CSiren           #y<--- #wCounters #y--->      #o4) #CDiablos
#o5) #CIfrit           #y<--- #wCounters #y--->      #o6) #CShiva
#o7) #COdin            #y<--- #wCounters #y--->      #o8) #CCarburkle
#o7) #CLuna            #y<--- #wCounters #y--->      #o8) #CGaia     

#cSyntax         - #yChoose #R<name>#y/#eNone
#cHow to Summon? - #y<name of #Rspirit#y>#n

SEE ALSO: #wHELP #y'DEITIES TRAITS'#w, #g'DEITIES TACTICS', #P'DEITIES BONUSES'
          'DEITIES CLANS'#n
~

0 'DEITIES CLANS'~
.
   The concept is simple. You and everyone else worshipping your deities consitutes
as being in a clan. Your goal is to bring all lands under the divine governrance of
your heavenly beings. But it will not be an easy task, since you will have to compete
against opposing deities members who has the same interests. But with the lands come
the power of stronger summons... along other things. But beware... as gaining more
power over the other deities leave you weaker against your major opposing one.

#wlands       - #oSee which areas each deity currently have control over.
#wobtain      - #oThe ability to invade and claim an area for your deity if not beaten in awhile.
~

0 'DEITIES BONUSES'~
.
#RIfrit   - +ve STR, -ve SPI, +25 Fire Resilience, 10% Fire Damage Bonus, 15% boost in melee damage
#CShiva   - +ve EVA, -ve VIT, +25 Ice Resilience, 10% Ice Damage Bonus, Water Swish ability
#wSiren   - +ve MIN, -ve STR, +25 Holy Resilience, 10% Holy Damage Bonus, (Free) Enhanced Absorb
#eDiablos - +ve STR, -ve MIN, +25 Dark Resilience, 10% Dark Damage Bonus, (Free) Devil Luck, Enhanced Final Blow
#gTitan   - +ve VIT, -ve STR, +25 Earth Resilience, 10% Earth Damage Bonus, 10% reduction in melee damage, earth wall
#yQueza   - +ve DEX, -ve EVA, +25 Thunder Resilience, 10% Thunder Damage Bonus, Bonus attacks and hitrate
#cLuna    - +ve SPI, -ve MIN, +25 Lunar Resilience, 10% Lunar Damage Bonus, Enhanced Lunar Shield and Lunar Blade
#oGaia    - +ve VIT, -ve DEX, +25 Natural Resilience, 10% Natural Damage Bonus, Enhanced Golem and (Free) Power Blow
#CCarb    - +ve LUC, -ve AGI, +20 Magical Resilience, 5% Magical Damage Bonus, 5% reduction in tech damage
#pOdin    - +ve AGI, -ve LUC, +20 Physical Resilience, 5% Physical Damage Bonus, 5% boost in tech damage

#P(*) N.B Elementals don't get some of these bonuses#n
~

0 'DEITIES TACTICS'~
.
   Care must be given in that you can't summon deities at will. Being in
war amongst each other, they expect their followers to do the same. As such,
they reward those who kill the followers of their foes while punishing those
who kill the followers of themselves and allies.
   The allies are split between good and evil as follows:

   #wThe forces of Good#n

#y1) #CSiren   #y2) #CShiva  #y3) #CCarburkle #y4) #CQuezacotl #y5) #CGaia

   #eThe forces of Evil#n

#R1) #LDiablos #R2) #LIfrit  #R3) #LOdin      #R4) #LTitan#n   #y5) #CLuna

   By killing an #eopposing follower#n, you get #P1 summon counter#n which can be
used to summon your deity in times of need. The exception to this is if you
kill your Deity #e#zworst#n foe, where you would get #P2 summon counters#n.
   Likewise, killing an #wallying follower#n will give you a decrease of #P1 summon
counter#n... and killing your own #w#zbrethen#n will be a lost of #P2 summon counters.#n
~

0 'DEITIES TRAITS'~
.
#yQuezacotl#n - Spirit which governs lightning. Appears amongst lightning clouds and
            showers the enemy with "Thunder Storm".

#gTitan#n     - Spirit which governs earth. Appears amongst beneath the earth and
            scatters foes with "Anger of the Land".

#rIfrit#n     - Demon Spirit that commands fire. Summons and then unleaches "Hell 
            Fire", a massive ball of flame that burns all enemies.

#LShiva#n     - Spirit which manipulates ice. Freezes surrounding objects with "Diamond
            Dust" and damages all enemies with extreme cold.

#wSiren#n     - Holy spirit of water. Silence enemies with "Silent Voice" before knocking
            them senseless with splashes of water.

#eDiablos#n   - Evil Spirit from the Depths of Hell. Protects its friends with the power
            of "The Darkside" before unleashing this same power onto its victim.

#CCarburkle#n - Playful spirit. Protects its friends from harmful spells with 
            "Reflection" while aiding in their recovery. Quite useful in fights.

#oOdin#n      - Warrior Spirit. Wields powerful "Zantetsuken" Blade which is rumored of
            killing victims with one slash.

#oLuna#n      - Mysterious Spirit. Descends from the heavens and haunt foes with the power
            of the night.

#PGaia#n      - Ancient Spirit. Rises from her earthly home to cleanse the world of evil.
~


0 'UNDEAD KNIGHTS'~
.
The Undead Knights where great knights fighting for good when they lived,
but a tragic twist in their life made them fail on some important mission,
and they have been cursed to spend eternity earthbound.

These creatures command many dark forces, and study the arts of necromancy.

#eKnighttalk     - #yClass channel.
#eGain           - #yGain access to the darker and more powerful magics.
#ePowerword      - #yThe most feared of the knights powers.
#eUnHolyRite     - #yHeal yourself with blood power. #w(5 Pkills)
#eGenocide       - #yDeadly attack with battle axe. #w(10 Pkills)
#eArmads         - #yThe Legendary axe that bring fear to the forces of evil. #w(25 Pkills)#n

These foul creatures are capable of using the #eAuras of #yCursed Rage#n.

Undead Knights also have the capacity to summon #yPOWERFUL #eskeletal steeds#n
from the abyss to mount and aid them in battle.

#eSEE ALSO: HELP #yAURAS, UNDEAD-ATTRIBUTES, 'UNDEAD LIMITS'#n
~

0 'UNDEAD LIMITS'~
.
   When they are left with no choice, Undead Knights resort to using the most
destructive and forbidden words available to them...

#eTerror         - #yFill a foe with terror, and preventing them to block/dodge for awhile. #w(Level 1)
#yLeech          - #eMany a warrior cower at this word due to its reputation. #w(Level 2)
#eOblivion       - #yPray for your salvation now... #w(Level 3)#n
~

0 UNDEAD-ATTRIBUTES~
.
   #y#uBonuses#n

#e- #yDeadly power words improve with Pkills
#e- #yMastery of Weapons improve Str and Dex with pkills
#e- #yMastery of Auras improve with pkills

   #y#uDisadvantages#n

#e- #yFairly reliant on power words.
~

0 NECROMANCER~
.
Necromancers are masters of the earth, dead, and of soul, living or deceased. 
#CPhysically weak#n, they rely on their powerful necromantic magic and armies of
zombies to protect them.
Necromancers also have the ability to summon VERY powerful guardians from the
nether realms to protect them and destroy their opponents. They can also train
their mind at super advanced levels, allowing them to cast attack magic that is
more powerful than mere mortals. The best necromancer can cast more powerful #rred#n
spells than a wizard.

SEE ALSO: #wHELP #yNECROABILITY, #cNECROSPELLS, #eNECRO-ATTRIBUTES, #wNECROLIMITS#n
~

0 NECROABILITY~

Here are the spells and abilities inherent to all necromancers.

[Necromancer Abilities]
   * #e#ROrder#n - #eCommand the undead to do your very bidding.
   * #eNecroDrain#n - Necromancers can draw energy from a corpse they are carrying and transfer
     it into their own body. This of course destroys the corpse.
   * #eMagetalk#n - This grants the necromancer the ability to communicate with other
     necromancers and spell casters in the realm as well as the Gods.
   * #eReduce#n - This spell allows a necromancer to lower the weight of corpses
     in his or her inventory.
   * #eGasCloud#n - Fill the room with deadly fumes intoxicating the living. #w(10 pkills)
   * #eShadowGrasp#n - Rip a foe from the netherworld and let the hunt beging...
   * #eSeek#n - Command your minions to seek your prey and bring them back to you.
   * #eReanimate#n - A master necromancer is as tedious to destroy as his followers. Even from
                 the grave, you can continue attacking your foes, but be wary as this cost
                 ALOT of mana. #w(20 pkills)#n
~

0 NECROLIMITS~
.
  * #eCorpseExplosion#n - Use your mystical powers to completely destroy a corpse, doing
    considerable damage to those who are in its way. #w(Level 1)
  * #eSoulchill#n - Smite a foe with the power of evil thus making all their damage do null
    for a few rounds. #w(Level 2)
  * #eMadness#n - Even Lloth herself cackles at the ingeniousity of this ability. #w(Level 3)
~

0 NECROSPELLS~

Here are the spells and abilities inherent to all necromancers.

[Necromancer Spells]
   * #eSoulblight#n - Using this spell, Necromancers burn straight into their victim's 
     soul, causing heavy damage and stealing away part of their life force for their
     own use.
   * #eDarkside#n - Gives the target of this spell incredible regenerative powers and a 
     large boost to their power.
   * #eDespondency#n - The opposite of Darkside, this causes the victim's soul to wither,
     dimishing its very life energy over time.
   * #eDark Kinesis#n - Causes the equipment carried by the victim to warp, possibly
     dropping it to the ground.
   * #eCreate Zombie#n - Any self-respecting necromancer prides himself in being able to
     animate corpses of the dead. While the zombie loses some power, its life energy
     remains the same as when it was living.
   * #eDark shield#n - Calls a swirling shield of evil to protect the victim, absorbing
     alot of the damage dealt to them.
   * #eDark Path#n - This spell vastly improves the necromancer's mind, granting him extra
     protection against harmful affects, and making casting of further spells cost less
     power and effort.
   * #eSoulbolt#n - A powerful and very efficient spell. This spell can be cast very quickly
     and also has a chance at hindering an opponent's movement.
   * #eEreshkigal#n - One of the legendary weapons that fell into the hands of evil...
     your hands...
~

0 NECRO-ATTRIBUTES~
.
   #w#uBonuses#n

#e- #wMasters of Zombies (able to summon more with more pkills)
#e- #wZombies' strength increases with more pkills
#e- #wMasters of Weakening a foe
#e- #wPowerful necros can use the #eCalling #wability

   #w#uDisadvantages#n

#e- #wHave AWFUL vitality and melee damage.
#e- #wHave weaker strength than most classes.
~

0 'BLADE LORDS'~
.
   Noone know the extent of their powers... why they have come... or what
they will do. But know this, they are capable of ripping you to shreds.
   The skills they are capable of are:

#CKakeio       - #yAttack a foe at the speed of Light.
#CFadedStrike  - #yAttack a foe with a fierce blow. (5 pkills)
#CPower Shot   - #ySmite down a foe with the power of Wind. (5 pkills)
#CPower Wave   - #ySmite down foes with the power of Wind. (10 pkills)
#CRaging Soul  - #yEntice your party's feelings, giving them a powerful boost
               for one round. (15 pkills)
#CSpeed Up     - #yMake ALL pulse timers go down TWICE as fast with this spell.
               (20 pkills)
#CSigma Rage   - #yBy concentrating on (a) random element(s), your party members
               can absorb those attacks. (25 pkills) (#wGood only)#n
#CVampire Fang - #yDevour your opponent's soul! (25 pkills) (#eEvil only)#n

#wSEE ALSO: HELP WEAPONS-ATTRIBUTES, WEAPONS-LIMITS#n
~

0 WEAPONS-ATTRIBUTES~
.
   #w#uBonuses#n

#e- #wMasters of Skills; Can use any Equipment skill they desire

   #w#uDisadvantages#n

#e- #wCan't wear any equipment.
#e- #wTorn between good or evil after 19 pkills.
~

0 WEAPONS-LIMITS~
.
#CEntice - #yAllows you and your party to do another armour skill. #P(Level 1)
#CRiposte - #yAllows you and your party to do another counter skill. #P(Level 2)
#CForestall - #yAllows you and your party to do another weapon and greater summon skill. #P(Level 3)#n

Take note that the affects of A and S groove #P#zWILL not#n work for these limits.
~

0 ANGELS~
.
   The Forces of Heavens is a mysterious thing indeed. Powerful enough to
destroy the entire universe, they seem strangely contented with the fact
of watching the fate of Mankind.
   However, at the Beginning of the Age of Confusion, Tyrael, The Arch-
Angel of the Divine Fist left his holy position in the skies and ventured
towards the Earth, fighting all evil which stood in his way.
   Many Warlocks wonder why Tyrael came to assist his fellow mankind. One
wise one suggest that either Tyrael felt that Humans can't handle the Evil
which is going to corrupt the World or even worse, He saw Heaven being
threaten by some unknown force which his holy brothers didn't see. In
either case, this is what happened.
   Eons later, in the middle of the Rebirth of the Apocalypse, there is
rumours of more and more Angels leaving their peaceful life to fight for
the Salvation of ManKind...

#wPray          - #LAngelic Communication Channel
#wMegaStrike    - #LA HUGE, powerful strike with the Sword of the Heavens.

   #wSEE ALSO: HELP #LENLIGHTEN#w, #LANGELSKILLS#w, #LANGEL-ATTRIBUTES#w, #L'ANGEL LIMITS'#n
~

0 DEMONS~
.
   These fiends are the damned ones. They have sold their souls in exchange 
for power, and they improve this power by draining the souls of their 
victims. Their powers are mysterious, but the following facts are known:

#R* #yMost demons are able to assume the form of a weapon.
#R* #yAll demons have protection against normal Offensive Magic.
#R* Inpart       - #yInpart demonic powers into you, inpart self [power].
#R* Revenga      - #yA mysterious slash only capable from the Revenge Blade...#n

#wSEE ALSO: HELP DEMONPOWER, DEMONSKILLS, REVENGEBLADE, DEMON-ATTRIBUTES,
          'DEMON LIMITS'#n
~

0 DEMON-ATTRIBUTES~
.
   #y#uBonuses#n

#R- #yMasters of Destruction
#R- #yMembers of the Heavenly Clan
#w- #LVery strong demons can wield the dreaded Revenge Blade

   #y#uDisadvantages#n

#R- #yWeak VS Good
~

0 REVENGEBLADE~
.
    A legendary weapon created by the forces of heavens but sealed up forever in
the depths of hell... Only the most powerful demons can tap into this power and
transfer his/her soul into the blade itself.
    Granting its wielder powerful bonuses, the blade can also be used as a 
substitute for any weapon required for techniques and is also capable of performing
some of the demonic commands as well as these:

#RDCurse   - #ySet your victim ablaze with demonic flames.
#RSoulHeal - #yUse your lifeforce to heal a target at will.
#RSoulLink - #y???#n

    This is a very dangerous weapon and as such those against it very existence must
dispose of it as quickly as possible.... or suffer the consequences...
~

