powerful affects on their equip. It costs some gold but is well
worth it.
~

0 MCCP MCP~
#CMccp#n is a compression protocol, and the two main benefits of mccp are:

1. Lower bandwidth use by the mud.
2. Clients (i.e. players) get large responses (such as, for example, combat
   spam) from the mud at a higher rate - the mud will "feel" faster, despite
   the fact that the actual round-trip times are unchanged.

With a suitable client, mccp is entirely transparent to the user - it
automatically enables itself when supported by both the server and client.

For more details on the protocol, your welcome to visit
#ehttp://homepages.ihug.co.nz/#p-#eicecube/compress/   #p*The dash is a tilde*#n

Currently the following mud clients are know to support mccp.

#w* mcl, a client for linux. Version 0.42.05 and above.
#y* MUSHclient, a windows client. Version 2.14 and above.
#c* Kmud, another linux client.
#R* Zmud for windows, Beta 6.03 and later.#n

To turn on or off this system if you wish to use it, type #wcompress#n at
your prompt. Note that is your mud client can't handle MCCP and you use it, it
may mess up your mudclient so be wary of this.
~

