0 SPECIALBUY~
.
   In Utopia, there are alot of ways to collect money: Betting, Bounties, Selling, Killing Mobs,
participating in quests, etc. But... what can one do with their hard earn cash?
   Well, your answers had been heeded and this is the result.
   Utopia's one and old shop is here to satisfy all your buying needs. From buying a variety
of items that can be used, the shop is almost positive that it will have what you so desire...
   The shop is highly expensive though...

   SPEND YOUR MONEY!!!

   #wSyntax: #CSpecialBuy     - #oTo Buy whatever item you want.
           #CUse            - #oTo use the items that you bought.
           #CSustain        - #oAn advanced using technique that releases the TRUE powers of the item.#n
~

0 'SCAVENGER HUNT'~
.
   Every #w25 #ypkills#n, the immortals will grant peace throughout the land, allowing
everyone to temporarily stop their quest for fame and power and to participate in
a scavenger hunt.
   Like most other quests, it is simple. #w50 #Citems#n will be scattered throughout the
realm and it is up to the players to find as #Cmany#n of these items as possible. The Hunt
will be for 8 ticks or until all the items are found, whichever one is quicker.
   At the end, #ygold#n pieces will be given for each item found and as a bonus, the person
with the most items will find himself/herself the lucky recipient of an artifact for 24
ticks.

   #wSyntax: #gScavenger                #w- #PTo Join
             #gCast Locate Scavenger    #w- #PTo find the location of these items.#n

   SEE ALSO: #wHELP #oARTIFACTS#n
~

0 ARTIFACTS~
.
#0the #RRevenge #0Blade#n       #w- #C15% extra damage given, with extra hitrate.
#cPendant of #wFaith#n        #w- #C15% less damage received, with extra parry/dodge.
#bIllumina Shield#n         #w- #CAbility to #wGuard #Cincoming attacks, with TONS of extra moves.
The #PCloak#n of #eDarkness#n   #w- #CAuto Darkness, with TONS of extra mana.
#wTooth of #RFenris#n         #w- #CEnhanced Damcap, Hitroll, Damroll.
#yThe Helm of Thor#n         #w- #CAbility to see ALL, even when blinded.
#eLord Soth's BreastPlate#n  #w- #CEnhanced Regeneration, with TONS of extra HP.
#oDragon #CStaff#n            #w- #CNullifies all Dragoon Attacks.
#eGrahf's #PM#pe#Pm#pe#Pn#pt#Po#n         #w- #CForce opponents to do your bidding with #wcontrol#C.
#CDragon #yBuster#n           #w- #CDoes crippling damage to Dragoons.#n

#eNote that with an artifact in your possession, NO safe skills work so be aware of that fact.#n
~

0 BRIEF SHORTFIGHT~
.
   #wBrief #c- #eCuts down on spam like misses, parries etc
   #yShortfight #c- #RThe Ultimate in cutting down melee spam. Try it and See :)#n
~

0 RESCUE~
.
   When Group Battles or Armageddon is on, players can use the Rescue command
on people to take the blows instead.
~

0 TRAINING~
.
   Utopia: D.O.A have the basic features of a typical Godwars mud. Here, you
knowledge of weaponry improves by fighting other creatures and players 
throughtout the land. All you need is the various type of weapon that you
want to train with, for e.g a slashing or piercing weapon. There are many
mob trainers who will spar with you until your weapon proficiency is at its
max. #yTrainer Bob and Trainer Mary are too of these mobs.#n
   You can also increase your Magical Knowledge, or Spell Level, by repeatively
casting spells of the same colour. You will know which spell is which colour
from the shade your eyes turn into. You are able to keep on doing this until
your spell levels are at max as well.
~

0 PKNOW~
.
   This command is for those impatient newbies who is ready to join
the pk feast. Just type pknow.... then join the fun.
~

1 POLICY~

* No spamming any channels:
  This is unfriendly and upsets people. The penalty for this is that the 
  offending player will be silenced for a period determined by the immortal.

* No multiplaying or playersharing. Penalty is reset or deletion of all chars
  involved.

* Be kind to newbies, being a total jerk to newbies are not tolerated.

* Purposely CRASHING of the mud.
  Deliberate crashing of the mud will cause you to be denied or possibly
  deleted and may even end up in your site being prevented from connecting
  to the mud (banned).  Your ISP admin might also be informed of your action.
  The ISP that runs this site will definitely be informed. 

* If your going to argue and bicker with someone, don't spambitch on any of 
  he other global channels or you'll most likely get silenced permanently if
  you do so.  This rule is enforced by the imms, and the imms will be the ones
  who decide whether this rule has been violated. Live with it.

** If you don't like any or all of these rules or policies leave this site.
~

-1 PROMPT CPROMPT~
This command allows you to configure your prompt.  The PROMPT command 
will set your standard prompt.  You also have the option of having a 
combat prompt, CPROMPT, which will appear while fighting.  If no cprompt 
is defined, the standard prompt will be used for both conditions.
The following options are available:

%a %A = Alignment (word/numeric)    %b %B = Block Meter.
%h %H = Current hp/Max hp           %g    = Groove Meter
%m %M = Current mana/Max mana       %s %S = Style ( Assassins )
%r %R = Room name/Rage              %t    = Fight Timer
%v %V = Current move/Max move       %x    = Exp 
%d %D = Darkness ( Drows )          %k %K = Ninja Ki/Kakusu ( Ninjas )
%G    = Gnosis Points ( Wolves )    %y %Y = Current Dragoon Spirit/Max Spirit
                                            Current Demon Trigger/Max Trigger
%f %F = Condition of opponent/tank  
%p %P = hp in stars/hp in bar       %q %Q = mana in stars/mana in bar
%c %C = moves in stars/moves in bar %T    = tension
                                    
To switch your prompt on and off, use 'prompt on' and 'prompt off'.
For some examples, type 'help prompts'.
~

0 PROMPTS~
There are many possible prompts, and everyone will have their own 
favoured setups.  However, to get you going, here are some examples:

Original normal prompt: [%x exp] <%h/%Hhp %m/%Mm %v/%Vmv>
Original combat prompt: [%f] <%h/%Hhp %m/%Mm %v/%Vmv>
Simple prompt: [%hH/%mM/%vV]
Vampire prompt: [%B Blood] <%hhp %mm %vmv>
Werewolf prompt: [%R Rage] <%hhp %mm %vmv>
Combat prompt: [%N:%F/%n:%f]
Stat prompt: [%xX] [+%pHIT/+%PDAM] [%cAC] [%hH/%mM/%vV]

Remember, you can switch between the default prompts and your customised
prompts with 'prompt on' and 'prompt off'.  Doing this will not destroy 
your customised prompts.
~

0 PUNISHMENT~
.
Punishment can be delivered on the discretion of the imm who feels that a player have
step out of bounds and needs to be disciplined.  Now if you have been punished by an
imm, #DO NOT#n try to have the penalty reduced or lifted by going to another imm.  You 
must plead your case before the imm who had punished you.  The imm can decide to make
the punishment even more severe than his first decision.  What is accepted however is
you may discuss your case before any other imm.  No other imm, unless directed otherwise,
should remove your punishment.

Punishment can be delivered in the following order of severity:

1. Permanent ban of site (Forever)  - serious
2. Permanent ban of site
3. Delete character(s)
4. Deny character(s)
5. Removes status, legend, skills.
6. Freeze character(s)
7. Silence character(s)
8. Paradox character(s)

The Imms

SEE HELP 'RULES'
~

0 'HELPING NEWBIES'~
.
Yesterday, I was saying how the MUD is here for fun. Not for a competitive basis. Before
you continue reading please take this simple test:

a) You find the MUD is here for a competitive basis.
b) You find the MUD is here for fun and player killing people in a fun way, including
your friends.
c) You're a friend of someone and break up your 'friendship' because you're too pathetic
   to realise that you probably play console games in real life and beat that friend up
   at them all the time thus ending your friendship because you're sad. "Because they
   killed me on a PK MUD."

If the answer is A or C. I suggest you don't play here. Anyway, if the answer is B you
should be helping newbies since it's non competitive. I can understand that maybe you
don't want to give away your aliases but I remember a time when I first started out.

I was convinced by my friends Simeon and Cary to play this new MUD called Savage Wars:
Utopia. I'd never played MUD's before but they offered to get me up to speed on them.
They taught me the very basics and at the time I seem to remember that the MUD was just a
great laugh. Over time, I realised as DOA came along the 'fun' disappated and it became
more of a competition.

Point is, newbies came and newbies went because no one bothered to help them out with the
very basics. I'm not saying that you should hand a newbie your aliases but because VoD has
customisation here and there people should be helped along. You have to remember if I was
never helped along when i was player you wouldn't have had the joy of killing me *grin*.

SEE HELP: 'HELPING NEWBIES 2'
~

0 'HELPING NEWBIES 2'~
.
I had people who helped me and taught me things about the MUD and that was how I learnt.
They didn't throw a bunch of aliases at me and say 'LEARN THESE' they were kind of like
well my friend does this, maybe you should try it and they were constructive. They didn't
outright say 'you suck' they were saying that I have to try different things and learn
how to better myself. Over time and practice I got better and you had someone else a
converted MUD newbie to fight. I will admit and be honest. Utopia has basically been the
only MUD I have ever played in my whole life because I was never interested in spending
ages to level up, I just wanted to have fun and kill people.

I'm just saying to take a look at the MUD and try to help fresh faces. You want people
to kill, right? Especially 'new blood' and if you don't help them, then they CERTAINLY
won't be staying.

If someone asks for pointers or help with Monks or what a certain technique does
you should take it upon yourself to help them. If you really don't like this then you
can either be punished for saying no to them or you can leave.
-Nima.
~

