0 SETLOGIN SETLOGOUT SETFATALITY SETFATALITY2~
.
   These commands allow a player to create their own personalised login,
logout and decap messages.

   For Login and Logout, Just type the command you want and then the text
afterwards which you want the rest of the mud to see. #w#zNote#n You #uMUST#n
have a $n in your phrase somewhere.

   For e.g Setlogin $n screams viciously at you as he arrived in this world.
will show this to the rest of the mud. '(playername) screams viciously at you
as...'  Note that the $n represents your name.

   Likewise, the Fatality message is similar except you need BOTH a $n and a $t
where $n represents your name and the $t represents the victim's name. Note 
that SETFATALITY is for the first line and if you want, SETFATALITY2 is for the
2nd line.

   To have the standard login/logout/fatality/title messages again, just type the 
various command with no arguments.

   #g#zNOTE:#n#g Please be very considerate when making your personalised
messages. If they are a bit too much, the player WILL get punished so you have
been WARNED!
~

0 SKILL~
Syntax: skill | skill <player>

This shows the target player's skill with the weapon they are currently 
wielding.

Weapon skill				 

 1) Totally unskilled.
 2) Slightly skilled.
 3) Reasonable.
 4) Fairly competent.
 5) Highly skilled.
 6) Very dangerous.
 7) Extremely deadly.
 8) An expert.
 9) A master.
10) A grandmaster.
11) A supreme master
12) An ultimate master

Note that these are only rough estimates; one master might well be 
slightly more skilled than another master, and so on.
~

