.
#e* Drowsight      -  #wLets you see all people and rooms
#e* Drowshield     -  #wShield your aura from others
#e* Levivation     -  #wSuper fly spell (automatic)
#e* Darkness       -  #wTurns a room complety dark to everyone else
#e* Drowpoison     -  #wFavour to grant poison & immunity (automatic)
#e* Drowfire       -  #wImproved faerie fire    
#e* Spider         -  #wCreates a drow spider follower (cast mount)
#e* Web            -  #wShoot spidery webs at your victim
#e* Glamour        -  #wMake your items appear more glamourous
#e* Speed          -  #wDrow quickness! (automatic)
#e* Toughskin      -  #wReduce damage due to toughened skin (automatic)
#e* Fightdance     -  #wYour weapon dances around parries.
#e* Luth           -  #wThrow huge mobs with the power of Lloth.
#e* Elamshin       -  #wGives extra attacks when you are in a wounded state. (auto)
#e* Drewst         -  #wAbility to remove a victim from objectform.
#e* Velkyn         -  #wAbility to go back in darkness in a fight.
#e* DarkDodge      -  #wUse the Darkness to enhance your dodging abilities.#n
~

0 'DROW SKILLS'~
.
   These dark elves are Lloth's most powerful soldiers, capable of destroying
great civilizations and possessing great knowledge of the UnderWorld.
   The skills drows are capable of are:

#eDischard     - #wPray to Lloth to allow her to remove a player's protection from the deities.
#ePandoraBox   - #wMay your best dreams or worst nightmares be derived from Lolth final's gift...#n

SEE ALSO: HELP #r'CLERICAL DROW', #e'MAGI DROW', #r'MILITIA DROW', #e'LLOTHS GUIDANCE'#n
~

0 'CLERICAL DROW'~
.
   These Drow spend their time scripturing their spells in the dim light of the catacombs, they often
write spells that will aid their friends and rarely write invocations to hurt their foes. Clerical drows'
duties are to make sure that their militia Drows are geared up and ready to cause mayhem amongst the
humans.
   Clerical Drows' spells are sorted into pkills. They are as follows.

#CLevel 1 Clerical

#wBless         - Cuts down melee damage based on luck.
HandBlast     - Hurts a person with a blast of demonic energy.
Heal          - Pray silently to Lloth for healing... but beware her wrath.
FlameBlade    - Transforms in mid air to form a blade with fire.

#CLevel 2 Clerical

#wAid           - Goes hand in hand with the Bless spell.
Venom         - Coat your blades with the deadliest of poisons.
Poison        - Strike down a foe with these deadly fumes.

#CLevel 4 Clerical

#wLolthPrayer   - Gives the victim it is cast upon advantages in battle.
Unparalyse    - Nulls the affect of hold person.
HoldPerson    - Paralyze someone with the power of Lloth.

#CLevel 6 Clerical

#wNeutralize    - The innate ability to get rid of poisons.
Bloodlet      - A mystical stilleto blessed by Lloth that weakens the foe.

#CLevel 8 Clerical

#wLolthStrength - Raises strength and other various attributes of the person.
Shillelagh    - A magical weapon that increases damage by merging itself with
                the target's current one. This lasts temporary.

#CLevel 10 Clerical

#wRaise Dead    - Can raise the dead ( players ) but severely drains power.
LolthWrath    - An offering to Lloth which weakens the victim.

#yDesperation Attacks

#gFlamestrike   - A flame strike. This requires the summoning of the FlameBlade. #w(Level 1)
#gCura          - Cures a persons critical wounds and negative affects. #w(Level 2)
#gCloudKill     - A toxic gas which poisons the victim. #w(Level 3)#n
~

0 'MAGI DROW'~
.
   These Drow spend their time writing offensive spells and spells that can be conjuganally used 
between a Militia Drow and a Magi Drow. This however drains the power of both the Magi and the
Militia.
   Magi Drows' spells are sorted into pkills. They are as follows.
	
#RLevel 1 Magi

#CBlur            - By using this spell you appear blurry making some melee attacks missing you.
LolthCharm      - By charming your victim you curse them into hitting you less...
Hex             - The ability to impair a victim's speech.
AcidArrow       - An arrow that burns away at the victims skin.

#RLevel 2 Magi

#CHorror          - This spell can cause the victim to flee.
GhoulTouch      - Anyone who is touched by this can be paralysed. (Auto)

#RLevel 4 Magi

#CVampiricTouch   - A spell that is based on melee giving the person some health for a period
                  of time.
EarthBlast      - Use the very earth against your victims.

#RLevel 6 Magi

#CIceStorm        - Barrage people with icicles of ice.
#CFireball        - A perfect replica of the human wizards' spell.

#RLevel 8 Magi

#CSpiderSummon    - Summons Lllth's spiders to aid you.
ShadowDoor      - An illusion which helps you to flee easier.
ShockingGrasp   - By shocking the victim you might luckily freeze them.

#RLevel 10 Magi
#CInvulnerability - A luck based spell which can make the odd spell miss you.

#yDesperation Attacks

#gChaosBlast      - Wrecks confusion in the minds of your opponent with this spell. #w(Level 1)
#gConfusion       - Can confuse creatures and at the same time make them flee. #w(Level 2)
#gShadowFlare     - Let your foe feel the power of Lloth... and burn in hell. #w(Level 3)#n
~

0 'MILITIA DROW'~
.
   The infantry of the Drows. These are the women and men that are on the very front lines of battle and 
their main purpose is to take the brunt of the battle heat. They can also work conjugally with a Magi
Drow to help defeat their biggest enemies.
   Militia Drows' spells are sorted into pkills. They are as follows.

#yLevel 1 Militia

#gLolthDance       - Do the dance of Lloth to slash the victim viciously.
Silver Jiv'undus - Cause pain to all those who stare upon you. ( Auto )

#yLevel 2 Militia
#gCatacomb         - Encave the victim.
Dagger Slide     - Thrust a dagger in your victim's chest. ( Auto )
Scout            - Use your warriors to scout potential enemies.

#yLevel 4 Militia

#gWaver            - With this, a Militia can appear invisible to the naked eye.
Shoot            - Use this command to fire an arrow at your foe.

#yLevel 6 Militia

#gOrbbLance        - An illusionary lance of black widow spiders created by belief.
Choke            - Use the covers of darkness to take away a foe's life.

#yLevel 8 Militia

#gOlplynirDro      - Charm your victim and steal some of their life for your own.
ShadowShoot      - A powerful arrow skill that rival those of the snow elves.

#yLevel 10 Militia
#gElghinn Wu'suul  - Sneakily convert the victim by the power of your mind to be backstabbed
                   by Lloth. ( Syntax - Elghinn )#n

#yDesperation Attacks

#gDemiDrow         - Summon a collective blast upon your victim. #w(Level 1)
#gFallenAngel      - Make your victim feel the power of the dark. #w(Level 2)
#gSeries Slash     - Slash across your victim wildly. #w(Level 3)#n
~

0 'LLOTHS GUIDANCE'~
.
   A Magi and a Militia make a good team. Infact when they are together they can use Lolth's Guidance
and fully worship her to create a series of DEVASTATING elemental attacks. Use these well Militia and
beware as it will drain both you and the Magi's energy.

   #eDarkStrike#n - The Militia strikes down with darkness.
   #wHolyShame#n - The Militia make you feel the shame of being apposed to holy.
   #RDancingFlames#n - The Militia initiates a flame dance.
   #yRoaringSkies#n - The skies roar as the Militia summon the thunder.
   #gTitansRage#n - The Militia causes the ground to shake beneath their victims.
   #LSwiftWave#n - The Militia summon a tidal wave to strike the enemy down.
~

0 FIENDS~
.
   Centuries after the presence of Demons in the world, the Demon lineage have changed.
No longer exist any pure blooded demons. The blood of demons have been tarnished with
human blood. These half human, half demon being however have not lost the character of
their ancestors. With demon blood flowing through their veins, they inherit the strengths
and powers of a demon. The demonic side is so much more prominent in them that it is only
right to call them demons. With human traces in their blood, their mental powers are 
stronger and very much smarter. Once again, the time has come for these hybrid to come
out of secrecy and rise up from hell and make the world its empire. 
However small there numbers are, many have sold their souls to join the ranks of this
army from hell led by their Demon Lord. Will you sell your soul to the Demon King and
enjoy the riches... or losses?

#RPowers
#wLifespan   - #eAn ability that acquired by Princes and high ranking demons to live longer. #w(10 pkills)
#wDemonform  - #eThe ability to release your true form. #w(10 pkills)
#wFalsePride - #eRaise your target's Str by lowering their Dex. #w(10 pkills)
#wDamnation  - #eCover a target with a Magic repelling shield. #w(20 pkills)#n

SEE ALSO: HELP #e'DEMON TRIGGER', #c'DEMON TRAITS', #y'LEGEND OF THE ALASTOR BLADE', 
               #R'LEGEND OF THE IFRIT GLOVES', #w'FIEND LIMITS'#n
~

0 'DEMON TRAITS'~
.
   Being half demons, these humans have the tendency of releasing their true powers in
their supreme form - the demonic form. However, with most of these traits lock away,
they must show their upmost desire to their rulers on totally dominating the Earth, and
all those living on it. Only then can they be bestowed these traits.
   For the rulers and leaders of the demonic army, take heed when granting these traits
to your followers, for you want them to be used for dedicated evil.
   The traits that can be bestowed on demons are:

Claws: Razor claws grow out from your fingertips.
Fangs: Large, sharp fangs protrude from your mouth to help attack.
Hooves: Feet transform into hooves.
Horns: Characteristics demon horns appear out of the side of your head.
Power: The strength of your demon ancestors courses through your body, improving the
       damage you deal.
Sense: All senses are heightened.
Speed: Move more quickly to dodge/parry and deliver devastating blows.
Tail: A long slender tail extends.
Toughness: Skin hardens and your defense is improved.
Wings: Wings grows, and allows the demon to fly.
~

0 'DEMON TRIGGER'~
.
   The true form of demons is what enable them to wreck havoc throughout the world of
Utopia. However, with these new breeds of demons, it is very difficult to sustain
this form if at all.
   Understanding this predicament, the Dark Lord himself reluctantly gave these
hybrids a trait called the #eDemon Trigger#n. This is a state that automatically
make those of demon blood transform into their true forms instantly.
   At first, a demon can only go into his true form for a very short time but as he
works on improving this #etrigger#n, he will be able to sustain the difficulties of
remaining in demon form for longer and longer.

SEE ALSO: HELP #y'LEGEND OF THE ALASTOR BLADE'#n
~

0 'LEGEND OF THE ALASTOR BLADE'~
.
   This demonic blade resides in a hidden castle within the #eVortex#n. Said to be made
by a regenade sorceror who sold his very soul for untold powers, it is capable of
allowing its user to execute rather punishing attacks. However, the true power of
this sword lies in the heart of it. For only with this sword can a hybrid control
his #eDemon Trigger#n and transform at will.
   Be wary however as there is a penalty to be paid to receive this power and
alas, it could be the final price the unprepared demon may pay...

SEE ALSO: 'ALASTOR SKILLS'
~

0 'ALASTOR SKILLS'~
.
   These are the fabled skills associated with the Alastor Blade. It is to be
noted though that these had to be learned before they are usable.

#RStinger - A swift, violent thrust to the enemy.

#RAirRaid - Hover in the air blasting dazzling electric ribbons at foes.
          #wN.b - #eRequires demonform and wings. #w(10 pkills)

#RVortex - Catapult into the enemy sending those close by flying in pain.
          #wN.b - #eRequires demonform and wings. #w(10 pkills)
~

0 'FIEND LIMITS'~
.
#RRoundTrip   - #yUse Alastor like a boomerang. #w(Level 1)
#yMeteorBlast - #RSend a blast of fiery energy towards the foe. #w(Level 2)
#RHellsWrath  - #yThe most powerful demonic ability of them all. #w(Level 3)#n
~

0 'LEGEND OF THE IFRIT GLOVES'~
.
   The Fire God, Ifrit, represents a sigil of Strength. For years he wrecked
havoc throughout the mortal and nether planes until he was sealed away by the
deities Undine and Odin into a pair of magical gloves. Later on, these were
stolen by the minions and hell and tainted to become a replicate of pure
evil. Now they lies within the mysterious passageways in the #yTemple of the
#RSun#n. To the lucky demon who find and wield these gloves, they can 
release a strength that was thought to be lost forever.

SEE ALSO: 'IFRIT SKILLS'
~

0 'IFRIT SKILLS'~
.
   These are the fabled skills associated with the Ifrit Gloves. It is to be
noted though that these had to be learned before they are usable.

#RMagmaDrive - A blazing uppercut that sends people flying into the air.
#RLungeKick  - Similiar to the Stinger attack of the Fabled Alastor blade. #w(5 pkills)
#RMeteorBlast - Send a blast of fiery energy towards the foe. #w(10 pkills)
~

0 DRAGOONS~
.
   Humans that have acquire the power of dragon spirits granted them their destiny to be Dragoons,
Masters of Dragons. With this power comes responsibility to protect both dragons and humans from each
other and live co-existantly together in peace. Dragoons spirits enables the wielder to acquire the
power of the only one dragon. With this power, strengths and weaknesses are also obtained. In the past,
there would be one dragoon for each of the five dragon spirits but the tides of time change and now
dragoons who have achieved much as a warrior and command well his arsenal of skills and powers are
presented with the opportunity to accept the dragon spirit that has been given. However, with this
great reward comes a price; a price that separates you from humanity both by your power and fear
of you. Eventually, dragoons who were protectors of humans and dragons became the hunted. 
Hunted by those who fear them....
Can you live a life on the run? Will you accept your destiny to be a dragoon?

#wPowers:
#yTransform  - #CRelease your true power at will for a limited time.
#yDragtalk   - #CDragoon's communication channel.

SEE ALSO: HELP #CDRAGOONFORM, #wDRAGOONSPECIAL, #CDRAGOONCOMBAT, #wSWORDSKILLS, #CSPEARSKILLS#n
~

0 SPEARSKILLS~
.
   #wJab - #CUsing a spear the dragoon has the chance to jab his opponent from a distance. ( Auto )
   #wTrip - #CUsing the spear, a dragoon can quickly put his foes on the ground causing the fall to injure
          the opponent. ( Auto )
   #wImpale - #CA nice finisher to give to an opponent after a dragoon has trip an opponent and quickly get in
            some good damage while they are on the ground. ( Auto )
   #wVirtual Spears - #CA sudden and deadly series of attacks to the opponent's upper region, doing 
                    considerable damage. ( Auto )
   #wSpearHurl - #CUsing the spear, the dragoon can hurl the weapon with immense power at an fleeing opponent
               causing grave damage. ( Auto )#n
~

0 SWORDSKILLS~
.
   #wRadiance - #CAt certain points during the day, swordsmen can use the glare of the sunlight reflecting
              from their swords to blind opponents. ( Auto )
   #wMoon Sword - #CWith a splash of Luna energy, the dragoon can create a vacuum with their sword
                draining health from their foes. ( Auto )
   #wWindSlash - #CBecause of the sheer speed the swordsmen used to strike their foes with the rapier,
               sometimes the wind from the slashes also slices through the victim's body doing more
               damage. ( Auto )
   #wDemon's Cry - #CA very powerful uppercut with the rapier, using the forces of darkness to do
                 some good damage. ( Auto )
   #wEngarde - #CPokes the opponent's weak spot at the right time inflict some serious damage.
             ( Auto )#n
   #wSword Clash - #CAggresive warriors can go through opponents' defense with a fury of quick attacks.
                 ( Auto )#n
~

0 DRAGOONCOMBAT~
.
   Out of Dragoon form, Dragoons are weaker than other combantants. However, they have perfected
special attacks call additions that they can use to lower the duration they stay out of their
true form. Master these well and let your foes shriek in terror Dragoon.

   #yDemonDance    - #CThe preferred attack of choice of the Legendary dragoon Rose and those who
                 want damage over SP given.

   #yBlazingDynamo - #CThe preferred attack of choice of the rogue dragoon Dart and those who
                 want equal emphasis place on damage and SP given.

   #yFlowerStorm   - #CThe preferred attack of choice of the dragoon king Albert and those who
                 want SP over damage given.#n
~

0 DRAGOONFORM~
.
   Once being given the power to #wtransform#n into their true form, Dragoons can show their
enemies the wrath of the Dragons. Now alot more powerful before offensively and defensively,
as well as being #Pimmune#n to all nasty affects like blindness, poison, etc, the Dragoon
can quickly take charge in the battle driving fear to those who oppose the cause.
   In the dragoon form, the renegade knight is now donned in special dragoon armor, of the
element he has chosen. Also, he now have huge massive wings which gives him alot more agility
and speed for his attacks and the weapon he is using is also transformed.
   Once transformed, Dragoons can either use one of their magical abilities or do one of
their special additions; the former costing mana which will be needed to cast the spells.
   It is to be noted that the dragoon can only be in his true form for a certain amount of
rounds depending on the current #ySP#n he has available as he will lose #w50 #PSP#n every
round.

SEE HELP: #R'FIRE DRAGOON', #L'SEA DRAGOON', #w'HOLY DRAGOON', #g'JADE DRAGOON', #e'DARK DRAGOON'#n
~

0 'FIRE DRAGOON'~
.
   Being the most destructive of all the elements, the #RRed Eyed Dragon#n represents an ideal of
sheer strength. Believing that might is right, Fire Dragoons like pummeling their foes with
a barrage of power moves; hoping to end the battle quickly before they get hurt themselves.

