0 'DARAMON MONKS'~
.
   These are samurais retired from active service in protecting the emperor. These
warriors dedicate the rest of their lives to worship the Buddha Gods and giving words
of advise to the new samurai warriors. One dark night, these monks were visited by a
vision. Giving them an ethereal sword, the vision told them to take care of it till
the time of the Apocalyse Rebirth. True to the vision's words, the monks took their
new job seriously up to an extent where the true Emperor honoured them with the title
#yDaramon - The Sword Keeper.#n
   And thus was the dull lives of these monks for hundrends of years until the demons
roam free throughout the earth again. Realizing that the time had come and the vision
hadn't arrived, the daramons began to despair but Oba-kin Huna told them that they
are the true warriors destined to wield and use the sword in battle.
   Strapping the sword onto their back, the daramons left their monastaries to once
again protect the True Emperor from all harm.

#CHum              - #yDaramon Channel
#CBalanced Techs   - #y10 pkills and up
#CResist Holy      - #yYou know what this aura does. #P(2 pkills)
#CResist Earth     - #yYou know what this aura does. #P(4 pkills)
#CResist Ice       - #yYou know what this aura does. #P(6 pkills)
#CResist Thunder   - #yYou know what this aura does. #P(8 pkills)
#CResist Dark      - #yYou know what this aura does. #P(10 pkills)
#CResist Fire      - #yYou know what this aura does. #P(15 pkills)
#CShining Soul     - #yRaise your party's resilience to 3 random elements. (20 pkills)
#CHeavenly Gate    - #yOpen the doors of the Heavens, making all healing techniques
                   do 2X for a limited time. #P(20 pkills)

#CSEE ALSO: #yHELP 'ETHEREAL SWORD', 'DARAMON TECHNIQUES', 'BALANCE', 'DARAMON-ATTRIBUTES',
               'DARAMON LIMITS'
~

0 'ETHEREAL SWORD'~
.
   The spiritual sword given to these monks for safe keeping is actually the property
of one of the most powerful samurais ever lived. The sword however has a life of it
own and is capable of calling for help in the Ethereal World from its master, 
performing deadly techniques.
   When not in use, the sword likes sticking itself to the swordsman's back, waiting
for the next action.
~

0 'DARAMON TECHNIQUES'~
.
   Throughout the many centuries of protecting the sword from evil, the daramons had
devised several techniques to assist them. also, they were granted special abilities
from the Buddha Gods in their new battle to protect the True Emperor.

   The Techniques are:

Chakra     - Pray to the Buddha to gain some of your health back.
BeadsShield - Utilize the inner powers of the Daramon's Beads to protect themselves
              greatly. ( Auto )
Stunner - Call forth the Ethereal Spirits to dazzle your foes with their brillance,
          stunning them.
Empower - Fill the victim's heart with the wrath of buddha, consuming their life energy
          as your own.
Tremor - Summon a beam of energy within the ground to Smash into your foe.
FlamingUpperCut - Summon an Ethereal Being to execute a flaming attack on your victim.
ChillBlast - Summon an Ethereal Being to execute a freezing attack on your victim.
LightningSlash - Summon an Ethereal Being to execute a lightning attack on your victim.
SubtleTouch - This power allows the daramon monk to cure his target from 
              aggravated damage faster than usual as well from the venom of the 
              Death Touch.
~

0 'DARAMON LIMITS'~
.
#CZinjaKicks  - #yA powerful foot combo which devastates the victim. #w(Level 1)
#yShockWave   - #CStagger your victim with a MASSIVE shockwave. #w(Level 2)
#CBuddhaStomp - #yShow the Wrath of Buddha on all of your foes. #w(Level 3)#n
~

0 BALANCE~
.
   As the Daramon execute their techniques in battle, they start to go in the flow
of it until they are perfectly aligned with the balances of the universe. In this
state, they can either do a more powerful version of one of their techniques or
summon the ethereal sword to do special attacks alongside the daramons.

   Syntax: #wExploder #por perform a Daramon Technique#n
~

0 'DARAMON-ATTRIBUTES'~
.
#PAdvantages
#7- #PExploder lasts longer with more pkills.
#7- #PMasters of the Resist Auras. (More with pkills)

#7Disadvantages
#P- #7Are reserved, which is a burden without exploder.#n
~

0 TOURNAMENT~
.
   This is where all the bad boys are... This is for those who think they are the elites... This
represents the biggest, and most highly anticipated set of battles the entire world wants to see
again and again - The King of Fighters Tournament.
   16 of the most strongest people will battle it up in mano en mano battles, which the winners
going up the ladder to face other winners... until only one is left.
   Do you think you have what it takes to stand among the elites like Kyo Kusanagi, K' and
Krizalid? Do you think you can handle the honour and prestige of being one of the most deadliest
and feared warriors in existence? If so, you MUST venture to the battle grounds and enroll with
the Enrollment Officer.

#wTalk - #gUse this to enroll yourself into the tournament.#n

SEE ALSO: HELP '#CBATTLE RULES#n', '#wBATTLE PRIZES#n'
~

0 'TEAM BATTLE'~
.
   Apart from the annual King of Fighters Tournament held each year, this battle is the highlight
of the arena. In essence, it sounds quite simple - a 4 on 4 battle. However, it has the following
features:

- Although it is a team battle, at any given time it will always be one person vs another. From now
  on, the active participant will be known as the #CFighter#n.

- Each team will start off with 3 #PStriker#n points. Everytime a #CFighter#n is eliminated, his/her team
  will be given another striker point for a total of 6 #PStriker#n points per match. However, you can't
  have more than 5 striker points at any given time. See Help STRIKER for more details.

SEE ALSO: HELP #PSTRIKER#n, '#CBATTLE RULES#n', '#wBATTLE PRIZES#n', '#RPOWER METER#n',
               #y'TEAM PARTICIPATION', #o'TEAM PROMPT'#n
~

0 'TEAM PROMPT'~
.
   Below is an example of the prompt team fighters will have in their battles for supremacy:

   #o______________________/#yR2#o\______________________
   #o\#R++++++++++++++++++++| #w4  #o|#R++++++++++++++++++++#o/
    #wJohn                   0 #CS              #wRamsus

   #o<+< #wPow #C3 #o(#y*    ) #PS: #C4 #o>+> #n

   This is an explanation of it:

   #R+++#n    - Represents fighter's Health in % form
   #wJohn#n   - Name of Team's 1 Current fighter
   #wRamsus#n - Name of Team's 2 Current fighter
   #CS#n      - Stands for SPECIAL Ko.
            There are also: K - KO, T - Timeover, G - Giveup, A - Assist
   #yR2#n     - Current Round is shown here
   #wPow#n    - No. besides this is the current Power Meter Level
   #PS:#n     - No. besides this is the number of strikers left.
~

0 'TEAM PARTICIPATION'~
.
   To participate in a team battle is simple. First of all, you must get a team involving yourself and
3 of your buddies. Once you have done so, make them all #wgroup#n with you in the SAME room then type
#yFORM #P<TEAM NAME>#n, where #PTEAM NAME#n is the name of your team (doh?).
   After this is done, team members can adjust the position they start in the fighting order by using
the #CADJUST#n command. One must note however that this shift everyone else from that position one down.
For instance, if the 4th member type #CADJUST #w2#n, he will become the 2nd fighter, the 2nd fighter will
become the 3rd one, and the 3rd will be the 4th.

   From time to time, powerful team members will challenge the best you players have to offer in a furious
contest. If you have what it takes to beat them, you may be rewarded GREAT prizes. The teams are:

#RFat#eal #CF#wu#Cr#wy#n #PTeam   - #gTerry Bogard, Andy Bogard, Kyo Kusanagi, Ryo Sakazaki
#yA#wv#ye#wn#yg#we#yr#ws#n #PTeam     - #gSeifer, Dole BraveHeart, Andria BraveHeart, Tyrael
#eNests #RCartel#n #PTeam - #gZero, Krizalid, Ron, K'
#CH#ye#Cr#yo#Ce#ys#n #PTeam       - #gBig Joe, Robbie Williams, Dante, Drizzt Do'Urden
#wS#et#wa#er #CW#Pa#Cr#Ps #PTeam#n    - #gCarth Onasi, Kyle Katarn, Darth Vader and Bastila Shan

   Also expect special challenges from these fighters from time to time as well:

   - #CShingo, #pAuron, #oRock Howard, #eTakuma, #wIgniz#n

   Good luck...
~

0 'POWER METER'~
.
    This is exactly like your groove bar, but in team battles... you can use it for
these things below as well as your usual dodge/retort/desperation attacks:

                 #w#u1 #RPower #yLevel#n
#wTabulate       - #gIncrease Striker points by 1. Max of 5.

                 #w#u3 #RPower #yLevels#n
#wHyper Mode     - #g10 rounds
                 50% damage ( from you ) increase
                 Ability to recover from skills faster

#wArmor Mode     - #g10 rounds
                 10% damage ( from you ) increase
                 50% damage ( to you ) reduction

#wCounter Mode   - #g10 rounds
                 Quick Recovery enabled and immunity to lagging attacks
                 Extra chance in countering Striker Attacks
                 Chance of countering Fighter Attacks

                 #w#u4 #RPower #yLevels#n
#wChain Mode     - #g20 rounds ( 100% Chain Bar )
                 Chance of 'Chaining': Ability to do next technique immediately.
                 Immunity to Dodge and Retort Meter effects.

                 #w#u5 #RPower #yLevels#n
#wInfinity Mode - #gClear all Timers
                Heals you periodically for 10 rounds ( 2% total HP each round )
                Invulnerability for the first 3 rounds#n

N.B/ Note that chaining an attack takes away 25% of the Chain Bar and make the move do 25% less damage.
~

0 STRIKER~
.
  A #PStriker#n is an active team member, one whom hasn't #w#zjust#n been eliminated yet, that can be #ocalled#n
by the #CFighter#n anytime to assist them in the current round. The #PStriker#n can do anything they
wish, however... it is restricted down to one command. These are the things a #PStriker#n can do:

1) Cheer - Give hope and praise to your #CFighter#n in their current struggle, raising their #RPower
           #yMeter#n by a percentage.

2) Taunt - Give insults and low blows to your #CFighter's#n opponent, lowering their #RPower #yMeter#n
           by a percentage.

3) Skill - Use one of your normal class skills or kingdom powers in battle to assist your #CFighter#n.
           For instance, you can choose to #wHeal#n your #CFighter#n or #RBlast#n his #eOpponent#n into
           the air.

  Note that a #PStriker#n can't do any of these things unless he is #ocalled#n by the #CFighter#n.

Syntax - #oCall #w<Active Team Member>    #PE.g #oCall #wRon#n

  One a #PStriker#n is #ocalled#n, they have a max of #wfive #yrounds#n to jump into the fray and #PStrike#n
If the rounds had passed, then the #PStriker#n will lose his opportunity. In either case, the #PStriker
#yPoints#n will be diminished by 1.

Syntax - #PStrike #w<Person> #CCommand    #oE.g #PStrike #wSomeones #CShiki Pure#n

#eN.B #y1st Fighter can call #wANYONE
    #y2nd Fighter can call anyone #wBUT #ythe 1st fighter
    #y3rd Fighter can call anyone #wBUT #ythe 2nd fighter, etc.#n
~

0 'BATTLE RULES'~
.

- All spell ups such as Mangara Blessing, Divine Strength, etc are disallowed and thus will be removed from
  the #CFighter#n as they enter the arena. This doesn't hold to the classes that can use the spells.

- A #CFighter#n can give up the match at anytime by typing #RGiveup#n.

- Leaving the arena facilities in the middle of a match can get the #CFighter#n disqualified.

- Each match is allocated a certain time limit. Once that limit is reached, there will be a #wTimer#cover#n
  and the winner of the match shall be determined by seeing who has the highest HP% remaining.

- While tempers can get high as a result of tensed matches, False accusations will still not be tolerated,
  and thus most likely will see a harsh response from Nests Cartel.
~

0 'BATTLE PRIZES'~
.
   These are the possible prizes participants can obtain from Nests Cartel and other sources if they are
successful in their matches:

#w1) #yCoin Tokens
#w2) #yStatus Tokens
#w2) #yPK Tokens
#w3) #yLionHearts
#w3) #yAuras
#w4) #R( SPECIAL )    ---> #wSust#eain #R<---     ( SPECIAL )
#w5) #yFree Kingdomstuff#n

#eNB #yNote that you can only win ONE of the Special Items.#n
~

